The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, Nov. 28 (PTI): An official survey has found that over 1.3 crore children in the age group of 6 to 14 were out of school in July-August last year, junior human resource development minister M.A.A. Fatmi said during question hour in the Lok Sabha today.

 Fatmi said 6.94 per cent children in this age group do not go to school. The laggard states are Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, Bengal, Madhya Pradesh and Rajasthan.

 Chennai (PTI): A 48-year-old man, who held a German passport, was detained on Tuesday on suspicion of being a Pakistani after he arrived from Frankfurt. Syed Akthar gave contradictory statements while being questioned on his arrival by a Lufthansa flight, airport and police officials said.

 New York (PTI): Former US President Bill Clinton will visit tsunami-affected areas in Tamil Nadu, Thailand and Indonesia in December as UN secretary-general Kofi Annans special envoy for tsunami recovery. Clinton will review progress in the tsunami recovery efforts over the past two years, visiting new permanent homes and schools.

 New Delhi (PTI): A consumer forum has directed the Indian Institute of Aircraft to refund the fees of two students who enrolled in a certificate course believing it to be a bachelors degree course, and held it guilty of unfair trade practice. A resident of south Delhi, allegedly misled into believing that the degree being offered was a BAe, paid Rs 1.42 lakh for the admission of her two daughters. 

 Vadodara (PTI): Vivek Bhandari has been appointed as the new director of the Institute of Rural Management, Anand, (IRMA). The board of IRMA met under the chairmanship of Y.K. Alagh and approved the appointment of Bhandari as the institutes director, official sources said. Bhandari, who is a professor of history and Southasian studies and is presently working with a college in New York, will be taking charge in May 2007.

 Sriganganagar (PTI): A quack has been arrested for administering an injection on a pregnant woman that led to the death of the foetus, police said. The woman was taken to a clinic which was being run by Vidyut Kumar without the necessary permits.




